Google I/O Extended Grand Rapids 2016 Registration Is Now Open!

Join the developer community this year at our 3rd consecutive Google I/O Extended in Grand Rapids! Held at the Harris Building in downtown GR, this event will be more “Googley” than ever. With a day full of live tech presentations, food, networking, games, Google I/O Live Streams, and a special after-party, it will be an experience you won’t want to miss.

Your registration will grant you a spot at the conference and after-party, which includes access to all of the event keynotes and sessions, conference t-shirt and swag, refreshments, lunch, and snacks throughout the conference!

This year the conference planning committee has formed the Google Developers Group of Grand Rapids (GDGGR).  Please check out our new website to follow us for future events!

events.name: Google I/O Extended Grand Rapids 2017

venue.name: Grand Valley State University: Pew Campus

events.description:
Join the Google community at our 4th annual Google I/O Extended in Grand Rapids. This year we are heading back to Loosemore Auditorium at Grand Valley’s Pew Campus. In response to feedback, this year's event will be free! We are preparing a day full of networking, local presentations, and the Google I/O Live Streams. The morning will consist of networking and local presentations, followed up by the Google Keynote at 1pm. Visit our website to see the full schedule as well as other helpful information.

EDIT: Boxed lunch will be provided. If you have dietary concerns please email [masked] by Friday May 12.

-- Please note, we will not be providing lunch at this year’s event. Instead, we will head out around 11:30 to enjoy what the local community has to offer. This will be a great time to meet new people and catch up with old friends. Click https://goo.gl/AqIQ3B to see some of your options. --

We hope to see you there!

http://ioextendedgr.eventbrite.com

http://gdggr.org/

events.name: Google I/O Extended Grand Rapids 2018
events.description:
YOU MUST REGISTER ON EVENTBRITE (https://goo.gl/bqbkxV) TO BE GRANTED ACCESS TO THIS EVENT.

REGISTER FOR THE EVENT HERE (https://goo.gl/bqbkxV)

Welcome to the fifth consecutive Google I/O Extended in Grand Rapids!

Google I/O is an annual event hosted by Google to highlight the latest in technology and product innovation. This covers topics such as the IoT, working with material design, advancements in mobile technology, and more.

Google live-streams this event and encourages other communities to hold live watch-parties. In Grand Rapids, we take this opportunity to stream the keynote from Google, but also to pull together West Michigan tech community. This year's Google I/O Extended will be hosted at New Holland Brewing's newest venue, The Knickerbocker.

The conference will be different from I/O's of the past, with a focus on networking, good food, and an atmosphere for learning. This year will not have a large auditorium. Instead it will feature a distributed configuration with many TVs to watch Google provided content, and smaller, intimate presentations (fireside chats) throughout the two day event.

We are selling general admission tickets on a per day basis. In order to attend, you must buy a ticket(s) on Eventbrite: https://io18extended.eventbrite.com .

Interested in speaking at this year's event? Please make a submission to our short survey. https://goo.gl/forms/zOLmqrlVURtZ0AKS2

For more details, head over to our website http://gdggr.org/ or follow us on twitter @IOextendedGR (https://twitter.com/IOextendedGR).

Shout out to this year's conference and GDG Grand Rapids sponsors and partners!

Gold Sponsors
-BravoLT
-Spectrum Health
-StartGarden

Special Partners
-Grand Rapids Extra Life

events.name: Barcamp 2019
events.description:
GDG GR is a proud sponsor of Barcamp 2019 - check them out!

***REGISTRATION SHOULD BE DONE THROUGH THE OFFICIAL BARCAMPGR SITE https://barcampgr.org/register/ ***

Please head over to the BarCampGR site to sign up and register for free - clicking "Going" through this meetup event will not get you added to the registration list. Thanks!

--

BarCamp is an ad-hoc gathering born from the desire for people to share and learn in an open environment. It is an intense event with discussions, demos, and interaction from attendees, usually centered around design & technology topics. If you're not familiar with what BarCamp is, we recommend reading the rules. https://barcampgr.org/

Although BarCamp started in Palo Alto, California, in 2005, the event has spread like wildfire across six continents and dozens of BarCamp events are held each year. This website focuses on the BarCamp that is held in Grand Rapids, Michigan. Below are details about this year's event.

Who
Anyone can attend BarCamp GR. This event focuses on technology and design, so having an interest in one or more of these topics is strongly encouraged.

When
August 9 & 10
Attendees can bring a sleeping bag and camp out overnight, or they can attend each day separately.

Where
DeVos Communications Center at Calvin College in Grand Rapids, MI. Not familiar with this venue?

Cost
Free! But everyone is encouraged to present something or get involved, even if this is your first time at BarCamp. We're very friendly people.

Schedule
You're free to come and leave as you want. No obligations to stay the whole time, of course

The specific sessions will be determined during BarCamp, all based on who wants to give talks and what topics are of interest.

Friday, August 9, 2019
5:00-6:30 PM - Check-in and Dinner
6:30-7:00 PM - Opening session
7:00-9:30 PM - Sessions every 1/2 hour
10:00 PM to midnight - after party
Overnight
All-night hacking, etc at Calvin College
There will be plenty of room to crash on Friday night, so bring a sleeping bag.

Saturday, August 9, 2019
9:00-10:00 AM - Continental Breakfast
10:00 AM-12:00 PM - Sessions every 1/2 hour
12:00-1:00 PM - Lunch
1:00-4:00 PM - Sessions every 1/2 hour
4:00-4:30 PM - Closing session
4:30-5:30 PM - Cleanup
